Yes are an English rock band who achieved success with 
their progressive, art and symphonic style of music. They 
are distinguished by their use of mystical and cosmic lyrics
live stage sets and lengthy compositions, often with complex 
instrumental and vocal arrangements. The band's current 
line-up since February 2012 consists of singer Jon Davison, 
guitarist Steve Howe, bass guitarist Chris Squire, keyboardist 
Geoff Downes, and drummer Alan White.

Big Generator is the twelfth studio album by progressive 
rock band Yes. It was released in 1987 on Atlantic Records' 
Atco subsidiary label (Yes' last studio album for Atlantic) 
and was the follow-up to the massively successful 90125 album.
